cs.AI, cs.LO, cs.CL, cs.PL, cs.CR 

This paper deals with reasoning and abduction in First Order Horn logic theories, which are topics that fall under the categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO), Computational Linguistics (cs.CL), Programming Languages (cs.PL), and Cryptography and Security (cs.CR). However, since the paper focuses on modeling these problems in Answer Set Programming (ASP), which is a declarative programming paradigm, cs.PL is less likely than the other categories. Additionally, since the paper evaluates its approach on a benchmark for plan recognition in Natural Language Understanding, cs.CL is more likely than cs.CR. Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.AI, cs.LO, and cs.CL, followed by cs.PL and cs.CR.
